    "source": {
      "note": "2026-07 audit: prior p0-p3/skill/burst values did not match GO/Amber Lv10 data at all (each hit off by a different, non-level-aligned ratio -- likely stale/hand-entered before the goCommit pointer was added). Re-derived from allStat_gen.json skillParam.Klee at commit 2937f8a80846b18c3495b7657c0bae5c78c82606, cross-checked against Amber avatar/10000029 talent[0].promote['10'] (identical). Added plunging (previously missing entirely). Renamed all hit_definitions_json keys/sections to match GO's real target paths (normal/{0,1,2}, charged/dmg, plunging/{dmg,low,high}, skill/{jumptyDumptyDmg,mineDmg}, burst/dmg) -- a leaderboard built with GO's own naming was failing with 'no hit definition' errors against the old hand-picked key names (hit1Dmg, chargedDmg, jumpyDumptyBounce (note: GO spells it 'jumpty', not 'jumpy'), sparksDmg). multKey lookups are scoped per-section by damage_evaluator_service.evaluate_build (talent_multipliers_json[path[0]]), so charged/passive1 duplicate the same p3_mult value rather than sharing one. Added passive1/dmg (A1 Sparks 'n' Splash: Charged Attack DMG with a permanent +50% Charged DMG Bonus baked in via the hit-scoped passive1dmg_dmg_ key, self_modifiers_json below; GO's asc>=1 gate and Homework-only lockBadge_mult_ are both always-true/1x for a standard built character and are not modeled separately) and constellation1/chainedReactionsDmg (C1: reuses the burst formula at 120% MV, pre-baked into chainedReactionsDmg_mult = burst p0_mult x 1.2).",
